 <p>Shehbahn - 56 Evoker <br>
Vis Veres (guild leader)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/01 5:44:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard Spell Nerf</span><hr size=1> There was a guy that ran 10,000 tests and posted the results on the General Discussion board.  He revealed a LOT of interesting facts, but the most interesting was the cluster effect that th RNG gives: The chance of failing or succeeding actually goes UP with each failure or success.<br>
<br>
Rather than a MUCH smaller chance of a successive failure (such as a fizzle) the chance of a successive one was slightly higher, up to 6 times.  Moving seemed to reset this effect.<br>
<br>
Now, 10K isn't exactly an exhaustive sample, but you have to admit its pretty impressive and will tend to flatten out any wierd spikes you'd get with smaller batches.<br>
<br>
At any rate I notice more fizzles and resists right after a patch EVERY TIME and it tends to flatten out after that.  Why it does this I suspect nobody left at Verant knows.  The more I watch them work with and post on this game the more I believe that the guys on the game now are NOT the guys that designed the game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/12/01 5:39:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard Spell Nerf</span><hr size=1> The problem is that at level 54, a level 4 spell should NEVER, EVER, fizzle.  At 54, a level 20 tishan's clash should never fizzle.  Hell, at 54, the only spells that should have even a slight chance of a fizzle should be level 49+ spells, and with my evocation capped, those fizzles should show up maybe once in 200 casts.<br>
<br>
If your sense heading skill is capped, why does it fail one in twenty times you try to use it in the 50+ range?<br>
<br>
This isn't like a melee skill, or when you are casting on a mob where armor class and magic resist rates will cause a lesser or lack of effect, this is just to USE the skill you have which is maxed out.<br>
<br>
<br>
btw, the gate spell has only started to fizzle after I got to level 50.  At 54, the fizzle rate is higher than when I was 40.<br>
